A <b>reentrant mutex</b> is a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../827/36827.xml">
mutual exclusion</link> mechanism.  In a reentrant mutex, the same thread can acquire the lock multiple times. However, the lock must be released the same number of times or else other threads will be unable to acquire the lock.
